SMCHR: Satisfiability Modulo Constraint Handling Rules
======================================================

This binary package is an implementation of Satisfiability Modulo Constraint
Handling Rules (SMCHR).  The package includes:
    * ./smchr.linux -- The SMCHR system [64bit Linux]
    * ./smchr.macosx -- The SMCHR system [64bit MacOSX]
    * ./smchr.exe -- The SMCHR system [64bit Windows]
    * ./doc/* -- Documentation.
    * ./examples/* -- Example CHR solvers.
    * ./test/* -- Test cases.
    * ./tools/* -- Some tools:
      - flatzinc: a FlatZinc to SMCHR translator.
      - answer: pretty prints SMCHR output for bounds/domain/LCG problems.

SMCHR (all operating systems) requires a 64-bit CPU, i.e. x64_64 or AMD64.
Please see ./doc/smchr.pdf for the full documentation.

